  "question": "Symmetric Cryptography",
  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Symmetric Cryptography Interactive Demo</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>Symmetric Cryptography Interactive Demo</h1>\n\n<p>\nThis demonstration explores <strong>symmetric cryptography</strong> concepts:\nencrypting and decrypting text using a shared secret key. You can experiment with multiple algorithms,\nkey sizes, input text, and modes to see how symmetric encryption works.\n</p>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>Step 1: Select Algorithm and Parameters</h2>\n\n<label for=\"algoSelect\">Algorithm:</label>\n<select id=\"algoSelect\" aria-label=\"Algorithm selection\">\n  <option value=\"aes-128-cbc\">AES - 128 bit key - CBC Mode</option>\n  <option value=\"aes-192-cbc\">AES - 192 bit key - CBC Mode</option>\n  <option value=\"aes-256-cbc\">AES - 256 bit key - CBC Mode</option>\n  <option value=\"aes-128-ctr\">AES - 128 bit key - CTR Mode</option>\n  <option value=\"aes-192-ctr\">AES - 192 bit key - CTR Mode</option>\n  <option value=\"aes-256-ctr\">AES - 256 bit key - CTR Mode</option>\n  <option value=\"rc4\">RC4 (stream cipher, 128 bit key)</option>\n  <option value=\"chacha20\">ChaCha20 (stream cipher, 256 bit key)</option>\n</select>\n\n<p><small>Note: Not all algorithms are natively available in browser crypto API.</small></p>\n\n<label for=\"keyInput\">Key (hexadecimal or ASCII):</label>\n<br />\n<textarea id=\"keyInput\" rows=\"2\" cols=\"60\" placeholder=\"Enter key here (ASCII or hex starting with 0x)...\"></textarea>\n<br />\n<label><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"keyHexCheckbox\" /> Interpret key as hexadecimal string</label>\n\n<br />\n<label for=\"ivInput\">Initialization Vector / Nonce (hexadecimal):</label>\n<br />\n<textarea id=\"ivInput\" rows=\"1\" cols=\"60\" placeholder=\"Enter IV/Nonce in hex (for AES modes or ChaCha20)\"></textarea>\n<br />\n\n<button id=\"generateRandomKeyBtn\" type=\"button\">Generate Random Key for Selected Algorithm</button>\n<button id=\"generateRandomIvBtn\" type=\"button\">Generate Random IV/Nonce</button>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>Step 2: Enter Plaintext and Encrypt</h2>\n\n<label for=\"plaintextInput\">Plaintext (UTF-8):</label>\n<br />\n<textarea id=\"plaintextInput\" rows=\"5\" cols=\"70\" placeholder=\"Type plaintext to encrypt here...\"></textarea>\n<br />\n\n<button id=\"encryptBtn\" type=\"button\">Encrypt</button>\n<button id=\"clearCiphertextBtn\" type=\"button\">Clear Ciphertext & Decrypted Text</button>\n\n<h3>Ciphertext Output:</h3>\n<textarea id=\"ciphertextOutput\" rows=\"5\" cols=\"70\" readonly placeholder=\"Ciphertext will appear here (Base64)...\"></textarea>\n<br />\n<button id=\"copyCiphertextBtn\" type=\"button\">Copy Ciphertext</button>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>Step 3: Decrypt Ciphertext</h2>\n\n<label for=\"ciphertextInput\">Ciphertext (Base64):</label>\n<br />\n<textarea id=\"ciphertextInput\" rows=\"5\" cols=\"70\" placeholder=\"Paste ciphertext to decrypt here...\"></textarea>\n<br />\n\n<button id=\"decryptBtn\" type=\"button\">Decrypt</button>\n<button id=\"clearPlaintextBtn\" type=\"button\">Clear Plaintext</button>\n\n<h3>Decrypted Text:</h3>\n<textarea id=\"decryptedOutput\" rows=\"5\" cols=\"70\" readonly placeholder=\"Decrypted plaintext will appear here...\"></textarea>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>Exploration Controls</h2>\n\n<p>Adjust key size, explore modes, generate or modify IV/Nonce and keys to see effects on encryption/decryption.</p>\n\n<label for=\"keySizeRange\">Key length bits (for AES algorithms only):</label>\n<br />\n<input type=\"range\" id=\"keySizeRange\" min=\"128\" max=\"256\" step=\"64\" value=\"128\" />\n<span id=\"keySizeLabel\">128 bits</span>\n<p><em>Note: Changing this modifies the algorithm dropdown to match AES key size with CBC mode.</em></p>\n\n<label for=\"modeSelect\">Mode (for AES algorithms only):</label>\n<select id=\"modeSelect\" aria-label=\"AES mode selection\">\n  <option value=\"cbc\">CBC</option>\n  <option value=\"ctr\">CTR</option>\n</select>\n\n<button id=\"applyAlgorithmChangesBtn\" type=\"button\">Apply AES Key Size and Mode Change</button>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>Information / State Debugging</h2>\n\n<button id=\"showStateBtn\" type=\"button\">Show Current Internal State</button>\n<button id=\"clearStateBtn\" type=\"button\">Clear All Inputs and State</button>\n\n<pre id=\"stateDisplay\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; border: 1px solid black; padding: 5px; max-height:200px; overflow-y:scroll;\"></pre>\n\n<script>\n(() => {\n  // Polyfill or utilities for encryption/decryption to support chosen algorithms\n  // Use SubtleCrypto for AES CBC/CTR, ChaCha20 not available, RC4 not supported natively: implement minimal RC4\n  // Fallback for ChaCha20 and RC4 with JS implementations.\n  // For simplicity and demonstration, only custom implementation for RC4 and ChaCha20 (simplified) are added.\n  // AES support relies on Web Crypto API.\n\n  // Helper: convert hex string to Uint8Array\n  function hexToBytes(hex) {\n    hex = hex.replace(/^0x/, '').replace(/\\s+/g, '').toLowerCase();\n    if (hex.length % 2) return null;\n    const out = new Uint8Array(hex.length / 2);\n    for (let i = 0; i < out.length; ++i) {\n      const hbyte = hex.substr(i * 2, 2);\n      const byte = parseInt(hbyte, 16);\n      if (isNaN(byte)) return null;\n      out[i] = byte;\n    }\n    return out;\n  }\n  // Convert Uint8Array to hex string\n  function bytesToHex(bytes) {\n    return Array.prototype.map.call(bytes, b => ('00' + b.toString(16)).slice(-2)).join('');\n  }\n  // Convert string UTF-8 to Uint8Array\n  function utf8ToBytes(str) {\n    return new TextEncoder().encode(str);\n  }\n  // Convert Uint8Array to UTF-8 string\n  function bytesToUtf8(bytes) {\n    try {\n      return new TextDecoder().decode(bytes);\n    } catch {\n      return '';\n    }\n  }\n  // Base64 encoding/decoding for Uint8Array\n  function bytesToBase64(bytes) {\n    // browsers have btoa for string, so convert bytes to string of char codes\n    let binary = '';\n    for (let i=0; i<bytes.length; i++) {\n      binary += String.fromCharCode(bytes[i]);\n    }\n    return btoa(binary);\n  }\n  function base64ToBytes(base64) {\n    try {\n      const binary = atob(base64);\n      const bytes = new Uint8Array(binary.length);\n      for (let i=0; i<binary.length; i++) {\n        bytes[i] = binary.charCodeAt(i);\n      }\n      return bytes;\n    } catch {\n      return null;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // RC4 implementation (stream cipher)\n  function rc4(dataBytes, keyBytes) {\n    // KSA\n    const S = new Uint8Array(256);\n    for (let i=0; i<256; i++) S[i] = i;\n    let j = 0;\n    for (let i=0; i<256; i++) {\n      j = (j + S[i] + keyBytes[i % keyBytes.length]) & 0xFF;\n      [S[i], S[j]] = [S[j], S[i]];\n    }\n    // PRGA\n    let i = 0;\n    j = 0;\n    const result = new Uint8Array(dataBytes.length);\n    for (let n=0; n<dataBytes.length; n++) {\n      i = (i + 1) & 0xFF;\n      j = (j + S[i]) & 0xFF;\n      [S[i], S[j]] = [S[j], S[i]];\n      const K = S[(S[i] + S[j]) & 0xFF];\n      result[n] = dataBytes[n] ^ K;\n    }\n    return result;\n  }\n\n  // Minimal ChaCha20 implementation for demo (not optimized, simplified)\n  // Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salsa20/ChaCha\n  // We implement a ChaCha20 block function, XOR with plaintext for encryption\n\n  function rotl32(v,c) {\n    return (v << c) | (v >>> (32-c));\n  }\n  function chacha20Block(key, counter, nonce) {\n    // key: Uint8Array 32 bytes\n    // counter: 32 bit integer\n    // nonce: Uint8Array 12 bytes\n    const state = new Uint32Array(16);\n    const output = new Uint32Array(16);\n    function U8to32(arr, offset) {\n      return (arr[offset]) | (arr[offset+1] << 8) | (arr[offset+2] <<16) | (arr[offset+3]<<24);\n    }\n    // Constants\n    state[0] = 0x61707865;\n    state[1] = 0x3320646e;\n    state[2] = 0x79622d32;\n    state[3] = 0x6b206574;\n    // Key\n    for(let i=0; i<8; i++) state[4+i] = U8to32(key, i*4);\n    // Counter\n    state[12] = counter;\n    // Nonce\n    state[13] = U8to32(nonce,0);\n    state[14] = U8to32(nonce,4);\n    state[15] = U8to32(nonce,8);\n\n    // Quarter round function\n    function quarterRound(a,b,c,d) {\n      state[a] += state[b]; state[d] = rotl32(state[d]^state[a],16);\n      state[c] += state[d]; state[b] = rotl32(state[b]^state[c],12);\n      state[a] += state[b]; state[d] = rotl32(state[d]^state[a],8);\n      state[c] += state[d]; state[b] = rotl32(state[b]^state[c],7);\n    }\n\n    for(let i=0; i<16; i++) output[i] = state[i];\n\n    for(let i=0; i<10; i++) {\n      // column rounds\n      quarterRound(0,4,8,12);\n      quarterRound(1,5,9,13);\n      quarterRound(2,6,10,14);\n      quarterRound(3,7,11,15);\n      // diagonal rounds\n      quarterRound(0,5,10,15);\n      quarterRound(1,6,11,12);\n      quarterRound(2,7,8,13);\n      quarterRound(3,4,9,14);\n    }\n\n    const result = new Uint8Array(64);\n    for(let i=0; i<16; i++) {\n      const val = (state[i] + output[i]) >>> 0;\n      result[i*4] = val & 0xFF;\n      result[i*4+1] = (val >>> 8) & 0xFF;\n      result[i*4+2] = (val >>> 16) & 0xFF;\n      result[i*4+3] = (val >>> 24) & 0xFF;\n    }\n    return result;\n  }\n\n  function chacha20Encrypt(dataBytes, keyBytes, nonceBytes) {\n    // dataBytes - Uint8Array\n    // keyBytes - 32 bytes\n    // nonceBytes - 12 bytes (96bit)\n    if (keyBytes.length !== 32) throw new Error('Key must be 256 bits (32 bytes)');\n    if (nonceBytes.length !== 12) throw new Error('Nonce must be 96 bits (12 bytes)');\n    const output = new Uint8Array(dataBytes.length);\n    let blockCount = Math.ceil(dataBytes.length/64);\n    for(let block=0; block<blockCount; block++) {\n      const keyStream = chacha20Block(keyBytes, block, nonceBytes);\n      for(let i=0; i<64; i++) {\n        const idx = block*64 + i;\n        if (idx >= dataBytes.length) break;\n        output[idx] = dataBytes[idx] ^ keyStream[i];\n      }\n    }\n    return output;\n  }\n\n  // AES encrypt/decrypt using Web Crypto API\n  async function aesCrypto(op, algo, keyBytes, dataBytes, ivBytes) {\n    // op: 'encrypt' or 'decrypt'\n    // algo example: 'aes-cbc' or 'aes-ctr'\n    try {\n      const key = await crypto.subtle.importKey(\n        'raw',\n        keyBytes,\n        { name: algo },\n        false,\n        [op]\n      );\n      const params = (algo === 'aes-cbc') ? { iv: ivBytes } : (algo === 'aes-ctr') ? { counter: ivBytes, length: 64 } : {};\n      const result = await crypto.subtle[op](algo, key, dataBytes, params);\n      return new Uint8Array(result);\n    } catch(e) {\n      throw new Error('AES operation failed: '+e.message);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Convert user inputs to appropriate algorithm params\n  // Algorithms we support:\n  // AES variants - with iv (CBC, CTR)\n  // RC4 - stream cipher - no iv\n  // ChaCha20 - stream cipher with nonce\n\n  // Elements references\n  const algoSelect = document.getElementById('algoSelect');\n  const keyInput = document.getElementById('keyInput');\n  const keyHexCheckbox = document.getElementById('keyHexCheckbox');\n  const ivInput = document.getElementById('ivInput');\n  const generateRandomKeyBtn = document.getElementById('generateRandomKeyBtn');\n  const generateRandomIvBtn = document.getElementById('generateRandomIvBtn');\n  const plaintextInput = document.getElementById('plaintextInput');\n  const encryptBtn = document.getElementById('encryptBtn');\n  const ciphertextOutput = document.getElementById('ciphertextOutput');\n  const copyCiphertextBtn = document.getElementById('copyCiphertextBtn');\n  const clearCiphertextBtn = document.getElementById('clearCiphertextBtn');\n  const ciphertextInput = document.getElementById('ciphertextInput');\n  const decryptBtn = document.getElementById('decryptBtn');\n  const decryptedOutput = document.getElementById('decryptedOutput');\n  const clearPlaintextBtn = document.getElementById('clearPlaintextBtn');\n  const keySizeRange = document.getElementById('keySizeRange');\n  const keySizeLabel = document.getElementById('keySizeLabel');\n  const modeSelect = document.getElementById('modeSelect');\n  const applyAlgorithmChangesBtn = document.getElementById('applyAlgorithmChangesBtn');\n  const showStateBtn = document.getElementById('showStateBtn');\n  const clearStateBtn = document.getElementById('clearStateBtn');\n  const stateDisplay = document.getElementById('stateDisplay');\n\n  // State\n  const state = {\n    algorithm: 'aes-128-cbc',\n    keyBytes: null,\n    ivBytes: null,\n    lastEncrypted: null,\n    lastDecrypted: null,\n  };\n\n  function updateStateDisplay() {\n    let s = 'Current Internal State:' + '\\n';\n    s += 'Selected Algorithm: ' + state.algorithm + '\\n';\n    s += 'Key (' + (state.keyBytes ? state.keyBytes.length*8 : 0) + ' bits): ';\n    if(state.keyBytes) s += bytesToHex(state.keyBytes) + '\\n';\n    else s += 'Not set\\n';\n    s += 'IV/Nonce: ';\n    if(state.ivBytes) s += bytesToHex(state.ivBytes) + '\\n';\n    else s += 'Not set\\n';\n    s += 'Last Encrypted (Base64): ' + (state.lastEncrypted ? bytesToBase64(state.lastEncrypted) : 'None') + '\\n';\n    s += 'Last Decrypted (UTF-8): ' + (state.lastDecrypted ? state.lastDecrypted : 'None') + '\\n';\n    stateDisplay.textContent = s;\n  }\n\n  function clearAll() {\n    keyInput.value = '';\n    keyHexCheckbox.checked = false;\n    ivInput.value = '';\n    plaintextInput.value = '';\n    ciphertextOutput.value = '';\n    ciphertextInput.value = '';\n    decryptedOutput.value = '';\n    state.keyBytes = null;\n    state.ivBytes = null;\n    state.lastEncrypted = null;\n    state.lastDecrypted = null;\n    updateStateDisplay();\n  }\n\n  function generateRandomBytes(byteLength) {\n    const arr = new Uint8Array(byteLength);\n    crypto.getRandomValues(arr);\n    return arr;\n  }\n\n  function parseKeyInput() {\n    const raw = keyInput.value.trim();\n    if (!raw) return null;\n    if (keyHexCheckbox.checked) {\n      // hex\n      const kb = hexToBytes(raw);\n      if(!kb) return null;\n      return kb;\n    } else {\n      // treat as UTF-8 string\n      return utf8ToBytes(raw);\n    }\n  }\n\n  function parseIvInput() {\n    const raw = ivInput.value.trim();\n    if (!raw) return null;\n    const bytes = hexToBytes(raw);\n    if (!bytes) return null;\n    return bytes;\n  }\n\n  function setAlgorithm(algorithm) {\n    algoSelect.value = algorithm;\n    state.algorithm = algorithm;\n  }\n\n  function parseAlgorithmString(algo) {\n    // For automation when changing key size & mode\n    // e.g. 'aes-128-cbc' -> { algo: 'aes', keySize: 128, mode: 'cbc' }\n    const parts = algo.split('-');\n    if(parts.length < 3) return null;\n    return {\n      basealgo: parts[0],\n      keySize: parseInt(parts[1],10),\n      mode: parts[2]\n    };\n  }\n  function buildAlgorithmString(basealgo, keySize, mode) {\n    return `${basealgo}-${keySize}-${mode}`;\n  }\n\n  // Fill algoSelect options from current keySizeRange and modeSelect for AES only\n  function updateAlgorithmOptionsForAES(keySize, mode) {\n    // We only update AES related entries in algoSelect\n    // Find AES options and adjust them\n    // We will update the three AES options matching the key size and mode and select first\n    // But simpler: just build new options list for AES and set selected accordingly\n\n    let selectOptions = [];\n    const basealgo = 'aes';\n    const ksize = keySize;\n    const md = mode;\n    // Construct options for AES for selected key size and mode\n    selectOptions.push(buildAlgorithmString(basealgo, 128, md));\n    selectOptions.push(buildAlgorithmString(basealgo, 192, md));\n    selectOptions.push(buildAlgorithmString(basealgo, 256, md));\n\n    // Remove all AES entries from algoSelect\n    for(let i=algoSelect.options.length-1; i>=0; i--) {\n      const val = algoSelect.options[i].value;\n      if(val.startsWith('aes-')) {\n        algoSelect.remove(i);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Insert new AES entries at top\n    selectOptions.forEach(optVal => {\n      const option = document.createElement('option');\n      option.value = optVal;\n      option.textContent = `AES - ${parseAlgorithmString(optVal).keySize} bit key - ${parseAlgorithmString(optVal).mode.toUpperCase()} Mode`;\n      algoSelect.add(option, 0);\n    });\n    // Sort them ascending keysize because added in reverse order (to add at top)\n    // Actually inserted from last to first, so reversed order, fix:\n    // Remove AES options again and add in correct order.\n    // But we only have 3 so just reset options by recreating entirely:\n\n    // Save other options\n    const otherOptions = [];\n    for(let i=0; i<algoSelect.options.length; i++) {\n      if(!algoSelect.options[i].value.startsWith('aes-')) {\n        otherOptions.push(algoSelect.options[i]);\n      }\n    }\n    // Clear all\n    algoSelect.innerHTML = '';\n    // Add AES options in order 128,192,256\n    [128,192,256].forEach(k => {\n      const o = document.createElement('option');\n      o.value = buildAlgorithmString(basealgo,k,md);\n      o.textContent = `AES - ${k} bit key - ${md.toUpperCase()} Mode`;\n      algoSelect.add(o);\n    });\n    // Then add other options back\n    otherOptions.forEach(o => {\n      algoSelect.add(o);\n    });\n    // Select the current algorithm corresponding to keySize and mode\n    const want = buildAlgorithmString(basealgo, keySize, mode);\n    algoSelect.value = want;\n    state.algorithm = want;\n  }\n\n  // On load, initialize keySizeRange & modeSelect from default algo\n  (function initKeySizeModeFromAlgo() {\n    const currentAlgo = algoSelect.value;\n    const parsed = parseAlgorithmString(currentAlgo);\n    if(parsed) {\n      keySizeRange.value = parsed.keySize;\n      keySizeLabel.textContent = parsed.keySize + ' bits';\n      modeSelect.value = parsed.mode;\n    }\n  })();\n\n  // Event Listeners\n\n  keySizeRange.addEventListener('input', () => {\n    keySizeLabel.textContent = keySizeRange.value + ' bits';\n  });\n  applyAlgorithmChangesBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const ksz = parseInt(keySizeRange.value,10);\n    const md = modeSelect.value;\n    updateAlgorithmOptionsForAES(ksz, md);\n    alert('Algorithm updated to ' + algoSelect.value + '. You should generate a new key as appropriate.');\n  });\n\n  generateRandomKeyBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const algo = algoSelect.value;\n    let keyLenBytes = 16; // default 128 bits\n    if (algo.startsWith('aes-')) {\n      const p = parseAlgorithmString(algo);\n      keyLenBytes = p.keySize / 8;\n    } else if (algo === 'rc4') {\n      keyLenBytes = 16;\n    } else if (algo === 'chacha20') {\n      keyLenBytes = 32;\n    }\n    const key = generateRandomBytes(keyLenBytes);\n    keyInput.value = bytesToHex(key);\n    keyHexCheckbox.checked = true;\n    state.keyBytes = key;\n    updateStateDisplay();\n  });\n\n  generateRandomIvBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const algo = algoSelect.value;\n    let ivLen = 0;\n    if (algo.startsWith('aes-')) {\n      ivLen = 16;\n    } else if (algo === 'chacha20') {\n      ivLen = 12;\n    } else if (algo === 'rc4') {\n      ivLen = 0;\n    }\n    if (ivLen > 0) {\n      const iv = generateRandomBytes(ivLen);\n      ivInput.value = bytesToHex(iv);\n      state.ivBytes = iv;\n    } else {\n      ivInput.value = '';\n      state.ivBytes = null;\n      alert('Selected algorithm does not require IV/Nonce or IV not supported.');\n    }\n    updateStateDisplay();\n  });\n\n  algoSelect.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    state.algorithm = algoSelect.value;\n    updateStateDisplay();\n  });\n\n  keyInput.addEventListener('input', () => {\n    const kb = parseKeyInput();\n    if (kb) state.keyBytes = kb;\n    else state.keyBytes = null;\n    updateStateDisplay();\n  });\n\n  keyHexCheckbox.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    // Re-parse key when mode changes\n    const kb = parseKeyInput();\n    if (kb) state.keyBytes = kb;\n    else state.keyBytes = null;\n    updateStateDisplay();\n  });\n\n  ivInput.addEventListener('input', () => {\n    const ivb = parseIvInput();\n    if (ivb) state.ivBytes = ivb;\n    else state.ivBytes = null;\n    updateStateDisplay();\n  });\n\n  encryptBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n    const algo = state.algorithm;\n    if (!state.keyBytes) {\n      alert('Please enter a valid key before encryption.');\n      return;\n    }\n    if (plaintextInput.value.length === 0) {\n      alert('Please enter plaintext to encrypt.');\n      return;\n    }\n    try {\n      const ptBytes = utf8ToBytes(plaintextInput.value);\n      let ctBytes;\n      if (algo.startsWith('aes-')) {\n        const p = parseAlgorithmString(algo);\n        const baseAlgo = 'aes-' + p.keySize;\n        const mode = p.mode.toLowerCase();\n        if (!state.ivBytes || state.ivBytes.length !== 16) {\n          alert('AES modes require a 16 byte (128 bit) IV. Please enter a valid IV in hex.');\n          return;\n        }\n        ctBytes = await aesCrypto('encrypt', baseAlgo + '-' + mode, state.keyBytes, ptBytes, state.ivBytes);\n      } else if (algo === 'rc4') {\n        ctBytes = rc4(ptBytes, state.keyBytes);\n      } else if (algo === 'chacha20') {\n        if (!state.ivBytes || state.ivBytes.length !== 12) {\n          alert('ChaCha20 requires a 12 byte (96 bit) nonce. Please enter a valid nonce in hex.');\n          return;\n        }\n        ctBytes = chacha20Encrypt(ptBytes, state.keyBytes, state.ivBytes);\n      } else {\n        alert('Unsupported algorithm selected.');\n        return;\n      }\n      ciphertextOutput.value = bytesToBase64(ctBytes);\n      state.lastEncrypted = ctBytes;\n      updateStateDisplay();\n    } catch(e) {\n      alert('Encryption failed: ' + e.message);\n    }\n  });\n\n  decryptBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n    const algo = state.algorithm;\n    if (!state.keyBytes) {\n      alert('Please enter a valid key before decryption.');\n      return;\n    }\n    if (ciphertextInput.value.length === 0) {\n      alert('Please enter ciphertext to decrypt.');\n      return;\n    }\n    try {\n      const ctBytes = base64ToBytes(ciphertextInput.value.trim());\n      if (!ctBytes) {\n        alert('Invalid ciphertext base64 format.');\n        return;\n      }\n      let ptBytes;\n      if (algo.startsWith('aes-')) {\n        const p = parseAlgorithmString(algo);\n        const baseAlgo = 'aes-' + p.keySize;\n        const mode = p.mode.toLowerCase();\n        if (!state.ivBytes || state.ivBytes.length !== 16) {\n          alert('AES modes require a 16 byte (128 bit) IV. Please enter a valid IV in hex.');\n          return;\n        }\n        ptBytes = await aesCrypto('decrypt', baseAlgo + '-' + mode, state.keyBytes, ctBytes, state.ivBytes);\n      } else if (algo === 'rc4') {\n        ptBytes = rc4(ctBytes, state.keyBytes);\n      } else if (algo === 'chacha20') {\n        if (!state.ivBytes || state.ivBytes.length !== 12) {\n          alert('ChaCha20 requires a 12 byte (96 bit) nonce. Please enter a valid nonce in hex.');\n          return;\n        }\n        ptBytes = chacha20Encrypt(ctBytes, state.keyBytes, state.ivBytes);\n      } else {\n        alert('Unsupported algorithm selected.');\n        return;\n      }\n      const ptStr = bytesToUtf8(ptBytes);\n      decryptedOutput.value = ptStr;\n      state.lastDecrypted = ptStr;\n      updateStateDisplay();\n    } catch(e) {\n      alert('Decryption failed: ' + e.message);\n    }\n  });\n\n  copyCiphertextBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if (!ciphertextOutput.value) {\n      alert('No ciphertext to copy');\n      return;\n    }\n    try {\n      navigator.clipboard.writeText(ciphertextOutput.value);\n      alert('Ciphertext copied to clipboard.');\n    } catch {\n      alert('Copy to clipboard failed.');\n    }\n  });\n\n  clearCiphertextBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    ciphertextOutput.value = '';\n    decryptedOutput.value = '';\n    state.lastEncrypted = null;\n    state.lastDecrypted = null;\n    updateStateDisplay();\n  });\n  clearPlaintextBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    plaintextInput.value = '';\n    decryptedOutput.value = '';\n    state.lastDecrypted = null;\n    updateStateDisplay();\n  });\n\n  showStateBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    updateStateDisplay();\n    alert(stateDisplay.textContent);\n  });\n\n  clearStateBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    clearAll();\n    alert('All inputs and internal state cleared.');\n  });\n\n  // Initialize display\n  updateStateDisplay();\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
  "messages": [
